e indicator is used to change the selected dot. The selection can be changed by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"simple tap gestures to the desired dot or by scrubbing the collection with a drag gesture."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The IndicatorView adjusts its size to the amount of dots. If the indicator cannot fit all dots,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the collection starts scrolling when scrubbing past the edges of the Indicator."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The IndicatorView is independent from any Pager, it can be used for any kind of page"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"representation through it’s index binding. However, if used with the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftUIPager\/documentation\/SwiftUIPager\/PagerView"},{"text":" that comes","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with this library, there are dedicated view modifiers, that provide convienient access to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"customize the PageIndicator."}]},{"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple encourages to think twice when deciding which UI Element to use in its Human"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Interface Guidelines. In this context an Indicator like this might not be the best tool when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"indicating the current selection of an element in a collection with many elements (which would","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"required too much scrolling).","type":"text"}]}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftUIPager\/documentation\/SwiftUIPager\/IndicatorView"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftUIPager\/documentation\/SwiftUIPager